TITLE: Implementing Server-Side Key-Value Store Handler in gRPC Java
DESCRIPTION: Server implementation of the create operation using synchronized access to ensure thread safety. Includes simulated write delay and error handling.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/blog/optimizing-grpc-part-1.md#2025-04-08_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
private final Map<ByteBuffer, ByteBuffer> store = new HashMap<>();

@Override
public synchronized void create(
    CreateRequest request, StreamObserver<CreateResponse> responseObserver) {
  ByteBuffer key = request.getKey().asReadOnlyByteBuffer();
  ByteBuffer value = request.getValue().asReadOnlyByteBuffer();
  simulateWork(WRITE_DELAY_MILLIS);
  if (store.putIfAbsent(key, value) == null) {
    responseObserver.onNext(CreateResponse.getDefaultInstance());
    responseObserver.onCompleted();
    return;
  }
  responseObserver.onError(Status.ALREADY_EXISTS.asRuntimeException());
}
```

