TITLE: Implementing Bidirectional Streaming RPC Client in Go
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to implement the client-side of a bidirectional streaming RPC named RouteChat. It shows how to send and receive messages concurrently using goroutines and channels.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/docs/languages/go/basics.md#2025-04-08_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
stream, err := client.RouteChat(context.Background())
waitc := make(chan struct{})
go func() {
  for {
    in, err := stream.Recv()
    if err == io.EOF {
      // read done.
      close(waitc)
      return
    }
    if err != nil {
      log.Fatalf("Failed to receive a note : %v", err)
    }
    log.Printf("Got message %s at point(%d, %d)", in.Message, in.Location.Latitude, in.Location.Longitude)
  }
}()
for _, note := range notes {
  if err := stream.Send(note); err != nil {
    log.Fatalf("Failed to send a note: %v", err)
  }
}
stream.CloseSend()
<-waitc
```

