TITLE: Implementing Client Work Loop in gRPC Java
DESCRIPTION: Main client loop that randomly selects and executes CRUD operations using a blocking stub.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/blog/optimizing-grpc-part-1.md#2025-04-08_snippet_2

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
void doClientWork(AtomicBoolean done) {
  Random random = new Random();
  KeyValueServiceBlockingStub stub = KeyValueServiceGrpc.newBlockingStub(channel);

  while (!done.get()) {
    // Pick a random CRUD action to take.
    int command = random.nextInt(4);
    if (command == 0) {
      doCreate(stub);
      continue;
    }
    /* ... */
    rpcCount++;
  }
}
```

