TITLE: Configuring Gson with Custom Base64 Type Adapter for byte[] Arrays
DESCRIPTION: Java code that configures Gson with a custom TypeAdapter to properly handle byte arrays by encoding them as base64 strings instead of integer arrays, significantly improving performance.
SOURCE: https://github.com/grpc/grpc.io/blob/main/content/en/blog/grpc-with-json.md#2025-04-08_snippet_10

LANGUAGE: java
CODE:
```
  private static final Gson gson =
      new GsonBuilder().registerTypeAdapter(byte[].class, new TypeAdapter<byte[]>() {
    @Override
    public void write(JsonWriter out, byte[] value) throws IOException {
      out.value(Base64.getEncoder().encodeToString(value));
    }

    @Override
    public byte[] read(JsonReader in) throws IOException {
      return Base64.getDecoder().decode(in.nextString());
    }
  }).create();
```

